# Chapter 2 literature review standards

## Critical synthesis (not summary-only)

- Each section must explain how prior work supports or constrains WheelSense design choices.
- Avoid definition-only paragraphs without analytical linkage to the thesis problem.
- Compare alternatives briefly when relevant (accuracy, cost, complexity, power, deployment).
- End chapter with synthesis that connects literature to architectural decisions.

## Citation discipline

- Use consistent citation commands tied to `latex/bib/refs.bib`.
- Do not mix manual citation numbering with key-based citations.
- Ensure every citation key exists in `refs.bib`.

## Section progression logic

- Use flow from broad context to specific stack choices:
  smart environment/AAL -> indoor positioning -> communication/protocols -> sensors/hardware -> software/data -> automation/AI (if in scope) -> chapter summary.
- Keep heading hierarchy consistent and avoid orphan subsections.

## Style

- Formal academic Thai with precise technical wording.
- Preserve consistent terminology across chapters.
